  "notes": "Zulu (isiZulu). Bantu language with three click series: dental (c/ǀ), alveolar (q/ǃ), lateral (x/ǁ), each with plain, aspirated, and voiced variants. Prenasalized consonants (mb, nd, ng, nj…) are single phonemes. Tone is high/low but not marked in standard orthography.",
